docs.lead_paragraph: A few months ago here on Motherlode, a guest blog by Allison Slater Tate caused quite the uproar. She wrote about being the mother of three boys, and how during each pregnancy she hoped she would be having a girl. Your response was spirited, to say the least, with some of you accusing her of emotionally abusing her sons (she is a friend, and trust me, she adores those boys) and others rallying around to admit that you, too, had wished for a certain gender and even mourned the child who was not born.

headline.main: Wanting, and Not Wanting, a Girl

docs.abstract: All parents harbor preferences, hopes and fears about who their children will grow to be.
